text: The Australian Ambassador to the Netherlands is the Australian Government's foremost diplomatic representative in the Netherlands. The Ambassador resides in The Hague. ==List of heads of mission== ===Minister to the Netherlands=== *Stanley Bruce (1942–1945) – non-resident (High Commissioner to the United Kingdom). *John Hood (Chargé d'affaires, 1945–1946) *Keith Officer (1946–1948) *John Quinn (Chargé d'affaires, 1948–1950) *Peter Heydon (Chargé d'affaires, 1950) ===Ambassadors to the Netherlands=== *Alfred Stirling (1950–1955) *Hugh McClure Smith (1955–1958) *Edwin McCarthy (1958–1962) *Walter Crocker (1962–1965) *Roden Cutler (1965–1966) *Colin Moodie (1966–1970) *Lloyd Thomson (1970–1974) *Frederick Blakeney (1974–1977) *David Fairbairn (1977–1980) *James Cumes (1980–1984) *Geoffrey Price (1984–1987) *Don Grimes (1987–1991) *Warwick Weemaes (1991–1993) *Michael Tate (1993–1996) *Ted Delofski (1997–2001) *Peter Hussin (2001–2004) *Stephen Brady (2004–2008) *Lydia Morton (2008–2011) *Neil Mules (2011–2015) *Brett Mason (21 April 2015–August 2018) *Matthew Neuhaus (August 2018–date) ==References== Netherlands Australia
title: List of ambassadors of Australia to the Netherlands
